{"type":"message","id":"df656450","parentId":"0ea1709b","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:15:30.316Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 13:15 GMT+2] EVOLUTION LOG & HFT STRESS TEST.\n\n1.  **Create Evolution Log (`docs_archive/EVOLUTION_LOG.md`):**\n    *   *Entry:* 2026-02-15 - Latency Optimization.\n    *   *Change:* Shifted Flash validation from Runtime (Price Check) to Build Time (Code Gen).\n    *   *Result:* 80x Speedup (~4000ms -> ~50ms).\n    *   *Rule:* \"No LLM calls in the hot path (HFT mode).\"\n\n2.  **Stress Test (10x Burst):**\n    *   Create `src/stress_test.py`:\n        *   Import `dmarket_api`.\n        *   Loop 10 times: `await api.get_market_prices(\"a8db\")`.\n        *   Measure average latency.\n    *   *Run:* `python src/stress_test.py`.\n    *   *Expectation:* ~50-100ms per call (excluding network jitter).\n\n3.  **Trader Code Check (`src/dmarket/arbitrage/trader.py`):**\n    *   Verify `async with self.api:` block is valid.\n    *   *Validation:* Static analysis via `pylint` or manual check.\n\n4.  **Output:**\n    *   Confirmation of `EVOLUTION_LOG.md`.\n    *   Average Latency (ms).\n    *   Trader.py health status."}],"timestamp":1771154130314}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a93edac","parentId":"df656450","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:15:47.614Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering Optimization Strategies**\n\nI've been mapping out the steps to create that `EVOLUTION_LOG.md` file. I'm focusing on latency optimization strategies, including the creation and execution of the stress test script to gather valuable data. Thinking about how the data can be used to improve performance, this could drive useful future iterations.\n\n\n**Prioritizing File Generation**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the `EVOLUTION_LOG.md` file creation within `docs_archive/`. I'm starting by determining the format for logging optimization efforts, including strategies and results. Next, I'll need to define the file structure to make sure data is neatly organized for easy review. I need to make sure I log everything in order.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771154147261_371","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Evolution Log\n\n## 2026-02-15 - Latency Optimization\n*   **Change:** Shifted Flash validation from Runtime (Price Check) to Build Time (Code Gen).\n*   **Result:** 80x Speedup (~4000ms -> ~50ms).\n*   **Rule:** \"No LLM calls in the hot path (HFT mode).\"\n","file_path":"docs_archive/EVOLUTION_LOG.md"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771154147373_372","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"src/stress_test.py","content":"import asyncio\nimport time\nimport os\nimport sys\n\n# Ensure src is in python path\nsys.path.append(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), 'src'))\n\ntry:\n    from dmarket_api import DMarketAPI\nexcept ImportError:\n    # Fallback if dmarket_api is not directly importable (mocking or adjusting path)\n    # Assuming dmarket_api.py exists in src/ based on instructions\n    pass\n\nasync def main():\n    api_key = os.getenv(\"DMARKET_API_KEY\", \"dummy_key\")\n    secret_key = os.getenv(\"DMARKET_SECRET_KEY\", \"dummy_secret\")\n    \n    # Initialize API (assuming constructor signature)\n    # If DMarketAPI is a context manager, we should use it as one, or close it.\n    # The instructions say \"Import dmarket_api\" and call \"await api.get_market_prices\".\n    # I need to check how DMarketAPI is implemented. \n    # For now, I'll assume a standard init.\n    \n    try:\n        api = DMarketAPI(public_key=api_key, secret_key=secret_key)\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Failed to init API: {e}\")\n        return\n\n    target_item = \"a8db\"\n    latencies = []\n\n    print(f\"Starting 10x burst stress test for {target_item}...\")\n\n    # Simulated loop if API isn't actually reachable or mocked\n    # But I will try to run it.\n    \n    for i in range(10):\n        start_time = time.perf_counter()\n        try:\n            # mock call if real one fails or method name differs\n            await api.get_market_prices(target_item)\n        except Exception as e:\n             # If it fails, print why (maybe method name is different?)\n             print(f\"Call {i+1} failed: {e}\")\n        \n        end_time = time.perf_counter()\n        latency_ms = (end_time - start_time) * 1000\n        latencies.append(latency_ms)\n        print(f\"Call {i+1}: {latency_ms:.2f}ms\")\n\n    avg_latency = sum(latencies) / len(latencies) if latencies else 0\n    print(f\"\\nAverage Latency: {avg_latency:.2f}ms\")\n    \n    if hasattr(api, \"close\"):\n        await api.close()\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    asyncio.run(main())\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771154147483_373","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python src/stress_test.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771154147606_374","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/dmarket/arbitrage/trader.py"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5125,"output":874,"cacheRead":2305,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5999,"cost":{"input":0.010249999999999999,"output":0.010488,"cacheRead":0.000461000